DOCUMENTATION
http://queatz.com/scge/documentation.html

INSTALLING

Install all the requirements:
python (3.1)
glfw (>=2.6)
GLEW
SOIL
freetype
ftgl
vorbisfile
alure (>=1.1)
openal
enet (>=1.3.1)

Debian: sudo apt-get install python3.1 libglfw-dev libglew1.5-dev libsoil-dev libfreetype6-dev libftgl-dev libvorbisfile3 libalure-dev libopenal-dev libenet-dev libeigen3-dev

If your repositories don't have some of the requirements you can find them here:

ENet >= 1.3.1
Source: http://enet.bespin.org/SourceDistro.html
Debian: http://packages.debian.org/pt-br/sid/libdevel/libenet-dev

Get Alure version >= 1.1 from here:
http://kcat.strangesoft.net/alure.html#download
Debian: http://packages.debian.org/pt-br/sid/libdevel/libalure-dev

To compile and install, open terminal from this directory and run:
./ultra
